<br>
PoP is the best thing that happened to everquest.<br>
<br>
Spells are hard to get, but at least I am getting them myself, not buying them from Bazaar from the uber guilds. Which means that I do not have to farm plat to sustain others raids.<br>
<br>
Grouping posibilities are really good. Xp is really good. Transportation is really good. Combats are short but hard. Mages look much more like the original mage. Pets rock. Nukes are adequate. Nice new summon items, specialy like the belt.<br>
<br>
Modrods are nerfed = good thing.<br>
<br>
AA are good. AA inflow is good.<br>
<br>
Good drops exists, although they are not easy to get. (The good spots are permacamped, would be nice if more good spots where available/known. Dificulty is adequate).<br>
<br>
Trials are VERY fun, although the timer of 30 mins sucks. Why can't they just let the corpse poof when the first person says &quot;return&quot; to the return npc instead of letting 30 wait outside for another 30 mins? That is 15 man-hours of wasted game time...<br>
<br>
